-- Packers Quarterback Aaron Rodgers Wins Most Valuable Player of Super Bowl
-- B y   M i c h a e l   S i l l u p
-- 2011-02-07T03:23:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-07/packers-quarterback-aaron-rodgers-wins-most-valuable-player-of-super-bowl.html
Green Bay Packers quarterback  Aaron
Rodgers  won the Most Valuable Player award for the Super Bowl.
Rodgers threw for 304 yards and three touchdowns as  Green Bay 
beat the Pittsburgh Steelers 31-25 to win the National Football
League championship.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Michael Sillup in Arlington, Texas at 
